  "prompt": "What are some lesser-known sights to see when visiting Icheon, South Korea?",
  "response": "Here are some lesser-known sights to explore in Icheon, South Korea:\n\n1. Icheon Ceramics Village\n- Features traditional Korean pottery workshops\n- Offers ceramic making classes\n- Showcases local artisan craftsmanship\n\n2. Seolbong Park\n- Historic park with beautiful landscapes\n- Features walking trails\n- Contains cultural significance related to local history\n\n3. Baeksa Museum\n- Displays local historical artifacts\n- Provides insights into Icheon's cultural heritage\n- Less crowded compared to major tourist attractions\n\n4. Icheon Agricultural Theme Park\n- Offers agricultural experiences\n- Allows visitors to learn about farming\n- Features seasonal activities and events\n\n5. Jojeon Martyrs' Shrine\n- Historical religious site\n- Commemorates Korean Catholic martyrs\n- Peaceful and contemplative environment\n\n6. Local Traditional Markets\n- Jungang Market\n- Provides authentic local shopping experience\n- Offers traditional Korean street food\n- Opportunity to interact with local vendors\n\n7. Icheon Literary Culture Center\n- Showcases local literary history\n- Hosts occasional cultural events\n- Quiet and educational destination\n\nThese attractions offer unique experiences beyond typical tourist routes in Icheon.",
